Polished request template

- What to convert (pick one and provide details):
  1. GitHub file — provide: owner/repo/path and optional branch (e.g., owner: customcoder245, repo: docs, path: guides/setup.md, branch: main)
  2. Public web page — provide the full URL
  3. Paste content — paste your Markdown or plain text here (I’ll convert Markdown to styled PDF)
  4. Images — attach one or more images to combine into a PDF
  5. Chat transcript — say “convert this chat” and confirm if you want the whole conversation or a selection
- Output filename (default: output.pdf)
- Page size and orientation (defaults: A4 / portrait)
- Styling and formatting options:
  - Theme: professional / minimal / code-friendly
  - Include cover page? (yes/no) — if yes, give title, subtitle, author, and optional cover image URL
  - Table of contents? (yes/no)
  - Page numbers? (yes/no and position: footer/header)
  - Add headers/footers text? (e.g., project name or date)
  - Include clickable links and bookmarks? (yes/no)
  - Font preference (serif/sans/monospace) — default: readable sans
- Delivery options:
  - Provide a download link in chat (default)
  - Or commit the PDF to a GitHub repo — provide owner/repo, target branch (optional), and commit message
- Anything else: special page breaks, watermarks, or accessibility (tagged PDF) requirements?

Also tell me:
- Desired filename (default: output.pdf)
- Page size (A4 or Letter) and orientation (portrait/landscape)
- Any extras: include a cover page, table of contents, or page numbers

Recommended defaults (if you don’t care to decide)
- Filename: output.pdf
- Page size: A4, portrait
- Theme: professional
- Cover page: yes (auto-generated title from source filename)
- Table of contents: yes (for documents > 2 pages)
- Page numbers: yes, bottom center
- Links/bookmarks: enabled
- Delivery: download link

Examples you can copy & paste
- Example A (GitHub file)
  Convert the README:
  - Source: customcoder245/my-repo/README.md (branch: main)
  - Filename: project-readme.pdf
  - Page size: A4 portrait
  - Theme: professional, include cover page (Title: My Project, Author: Jane Doe)
  - Table of contents: yes, page numbers: yes, links/bookmarks: yes
  - Delivery: provide download link

- Example B (Paste Markdown)
  Here’s my Markdown to convert:
  ---
  # Product Overview
  Blah blah...
  ---
  Options: output.pdf, Letter/portrait, minimal theme, no cover, include page numbers footer-right, deliver download link

- Example C (Images)
  Combine three images into a single PDF:
  - Images: attach image1.jpg, image2.png, image3.jpg
  - Filename: photos.pdf
  - Orientation: landscape, page size: A4
  - Add captions from filenames: yes
  - Delivery: download link

What I’ll do after you send the details
- Convert the specified content into a well-formatted PDF using the options you pick.
- Optimize layout (headers, fonts, margins), generate a clickable table of contents when requested, and embed links/bookmarks.
- Provide a secure download link in chat (or commit to your GitHub repo if you requested that).
- If there are any small issues (images too large, external links broken), I’ll report them and suggest fixes.

Go ahead — paste the source or pick one of the examples and tell me the options you want. I’ll start creating your PDF right away.